data.name: EUReturnPolicy
data.value:
Right of Withdrawal
As per European law, if you as a consumer have ordered something from mywinlife.com and are located in the Netherlands, Belgium, Germany or United Kingdom, you have a right to cancel your contract within 14 calendar days under your right of withdrawal. You are not required to provide a reason. Please note: Withdrawal is only possible if you have not broken the seal on our products.

If you exercise this right, we will refund the monies you have paid against the return of any products, business manuals, kits, training and promotional materials purchased within 14 days provided the goods remain unsold by you, are in the same conditions as supplied to you and are returned to the Company (at the address below) within 14 days of initiating the agreement. Any cost in returning the goods to WIN will fall upon you.

How to Exercise this Right
To exercise your right of withdrawal, you can notify us with an unequivocal statement in writing informing us of your decision to withdraw. This notice can be sent by email or letter to WIN Worldwide BV, Kruisweg 583, 213 NA Hoofddorp, Netherlands, support@mywinlife.com by supplying us with the following information:

  • Your name
  • Your complete address
  • The date you entered into the agreement (order)
  • Your order number
  • Your decision to cancel your agreement (order)


If you choose to withdraw, we will immediately send you an acknowledgement email of your decision. The 14-day time period starts on the date your order is shipped. To meet the withdrawal deadline, you must notify us of your decision to withdraw before the withdrawal period has expired and should then return the corresponding products to us within 14 days. You are responsible for the costs of returning the products.

If you have sent us this notice within the applicable time frame, your payment will be reimbursed within 14 days. Your reimbursement will include all payments that you have made to us up to the time of your withdrawal notice, which includes standard shipping costs. If you opted for a more expensive, expedited shipping method, you will be responsible for the additional costs associated with that choice. We will pay you back with the same payment method you used for the original payment, unless have you expressly agreed to a different form of reimbursement. In any case, we will not charge you a fee for the reimbursement. Notwithstanding this, we are allowed to withhold reimbursement until we have received the corresponding products, or you have demonstrated that you have returned the products, whichever date is first.

WIN Worldwide BV — United Kingdom
Independent Brand Partner Agreement

WIN Worldwide BV of the address set out overleaf (hereinafter “WIN”) promotes this selling system. Under this system, transactions are effected by participants in the system as principals. The goods which are sold under this system are the nutritional, skin care, weight management and personal care products manufactured or supplied by WIN and such other products as WIN may market from time to time (“products”).

Appointment of Independent Brand Partner (hereinafter “Distributor”)

  1. The applicant named on the application form overleaf is hereby appointed (subject to Clause 2) as a Distributor of WIN and has the right to sell WIN products on the terms and conditions set out in this agreement (the “Agreement”). In order to earn commissions, the Distributor understands that he/she must meet the published requirements.

  2. Corporations, partnerships and/or trusts may be appointed as Distributors of WIN at the discretion of WIN only when this Agreement is accompanied by a duly completed WIN Corporation, Partnership, Trust or DBA Information Form and copies of the documents specified on that form.

  3. The Distributor hereby confirms that he is over 18 and that he is the only WIN Distributor in his immediate family or household, and does not hold a beneficial interest in any other WIN distributorship entity.

    Distributorship

  4. The Distributor confirms that neither WIN nor any sponsor(s) has made any claims of guaranteed earnings or representations of anticipated earnings that might result from the Distributor’s efforts as a Distributor and understands that success as a Distributor is directly dependent on the Distributor’s own efforts in retail sales, service and the development of a marketing network. The grant of a distributorship does not constitute the sale of a franchise or a distributorship, and no fees or investment other than the purchase of the Launch Kit, which is sold at company cost and contains sales materials not for resale, have been or will be required from the Distributor for the right to market and sell WIN products pursuant to this Agreement.

  5. No purchase of WIN products or services is necessary to become a WIN distributor other than the purchase of a the Launch Kit, which is sold at company cost and contains sales materials not for resale. The Distributor’s Application and Agreement to become a WIN Distributor must be accompanied by the current fee for this purchase (not exceeding £200 including VAT) and the Distributor confirms that he has received access to the Launch Kit. Furthermore, Distributor acknowledges that the WIN Policies & Procedures, Advertising Policy and other service terms are and have been accessible to review upon request from WIN. The only financial obligation of the Distributor during the period of 12 months from the commencement date of the Agreement is to purchase the WIN Launch Kit at a cost of 129 and, if the Distributor elects to renew the Agreement, the payment of the annual renewal fee. The Distributor has no further annual financial obligation and in particular has a free choice whether or not to purchase any goods or services under this trading scheme.

    Distributor’s Obligations and Restrictions

  6. The Distributor has no power or authority to negotiate or incur any debt, obligation, or liability on behalf of WIN in any manner or for any purpose.

  7. The Distributor shall make no statements, disclosures, or representations in selling WIN’s goods and services or in the sponsor of other prospective distributors other than those contained in approved WIN literature.

  8. I understand and agree to honor WIN’s 100% unconditional moneyback guarantee to all retail customers, which states that any retail customer who is dissatisfied with a WIN product for any reason may return the product to me, within thirty (30) days of the purchase from me, for either a replacement or a full refund of the purchase price. I understand that the WIN Corporate Office will replace the returned product to me (at no cost to me), provided that all conditions of WIN’s Return Policy are met. I further understand that WIN will not refund to me the purchase price of any retail customer returns.

  9. All orders submitted by the Distributor to WIN shall be accompanied by money order, cashier’s cheque, a copy of a bank’s verification of wire transfer, personal cheque, or credit card information for the full amount due. All orders are subject to acceptance by WIN and the terms of this Agreement. The Distributor may not pay or agree to pay to WIN or any other Distributor a sum in excess of £200 in the first seven days of his/her appointment as a Distributor, whether in respect of products ordered or anything else.

  10. I will not use the WIN trade name, logo, copyrighted material, trademarks or service marks except in materials provided by WIN. I understand that unauthorized use or duplication of WIN trademarks, trade names or copyrighted materials is a violation of federal law, as well as WIN Policies & Procedures. Upon termination of this Agreement, for any cause or reason, I agree to immediately discontinue using all trade names, trademarks, service marks, printed literature, sales aids and film or video sales presentations theretofore provided me by the Company and understand and agree that any violation of this clause will render me liable to the Company for infringement of its trade names, trademarks, service marks, copyrights and trade materials.

  11. WIN may use the Distributor’s name, likeness, voice, biographical information and the materials supplied by the Distributor for purposes of advertising, publicity and sales promotion; this will not violate the rights of any person or organisation and WIN will not incur any liability for payment to any person or organisation.

    Sponsorship

  12. I agree to ensure that any prospective Distributor sponsored or dual sponsored by me receives the WIN Policies & Procedures and the WIN Compensation Plan prior to submission of the Distributor Application and Agreement and I understand that I am responsible for training and supporting the Distributor(s) I sponsor into WIN.

  13. I understand that I may apply to acquire a dual sponsor if this agreement is accompanied by a completed Dual Sponsoring Agreement and when I have attained the effective rank of Bronze or above in the WIN compensation plan. I also understand that I may be part of a dual sponsored downline (i.e. if someone upline of me is dual sponsored) or that I may become a dual sponsored distributor (or part of their subsequent dual sponsored downline) due to the termination and subsequent roll up of a distributor’s downline.

    Term and Termination

  14. A Distributorship is valid for one (1) year from the date this Agreement is signed, if accepted by WIN. Distributors are required to apply to renew their Distributorship annually in order to maintain their status as a Distributor as well as any rights and privileges of the Distributorship, according to the following terms and conditions.

    a) Each Distributor must complete and submit a Renewal Application and pay the applicable Renewal Application Fee in order to apply to renew this Agreement. Submission of the Renewal Application and payment of the Renewal Application Fee is due one (1) year from the date of the signing of the original Agreement, and, as applicable, on each anniversary of that date. All Distributors are required to pay the Renewal Application Fee. The annual Renewal Application Fee is payable to WIN.
    b) WIN has absolute discretion to deny any Renewal Application from any Distributor, for any reason or no reason at all. In the event that WIN denies a Renewal Application, the Distributorship will be terminated, and the Distributor will no longer have the rights and privileges of a Distributor. If a payment has been made, it will be refunded, unless applied to an outstanding debt of the Distributor, along with a written notice of the rejection from WIN.
    c) In the event that a Distributor does not submit a Renewal Application and pay the Renewal Application Fee by the date due, then the Distributor forfeits his rights and benefits as of that date and WIN may automatically terminate the Distributorship without notice.

  15. Either WIN or the Distributor may terminate this Agreement at any time with or without notice and without penalty by giving written notice to the other party at its address set out overleaf. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the applicable party may terminate this Agreement at any time, by written notice to the other party, upon the occurrence of any of the following: The instigation of any action, suit or proceeding, or the adoption or issuance of any law, regulation, ruling or determination, including but not limited to any regulation, ruling or determination of the FCC or any public utility commission or other state regulatory agency, which has a substantial likelihood of materially and adversely affecting the business of WIN.

  16. The Distributor has the right without penalty within 14 days of entering into this Agreement to cancel it with immediate effect by giving written notice to WIN utilizing the form in BackOffice or by an unequivocal statement addressed to: WIN Worldwide BV, Kruisweg 583, 2132 NA Hoofddorp, Netherlands, support@mywinlife.com, in which case the Distributor has the right:

    a) to recover any monies which the Distributor has paid to or for the benefit of WIN in connection with the Distributor’s participation in this selling system or paid to any other Distributor in accordance with the provisions of this selling system; and
    b) to return to WIN (at the address of WIN Worldwide BV Product Returns, Kruisweg 583, 2132 NA Hoofddorp, The Netherlands) upon receipt of a Return Merchandise Authorisation any goods which the Distributor has purchased within that period under this selling system and which remain unsold provided that such unsold goods remain in the condition in which they were in at the time of purchase (except their external wrappings may have been broken) and to recover any monies paid in respect of such goods; and
    c) to cancel any services which the Distributor has ordered within that period under this selling system and to recover any monies paid in respect of such services not yet supplied to them.

  17. In order to recover any monies under paragraphs 16(a) or (c) above the Distributor must give written notice requesting the repayment of such monies to WIN at its address set out on this form within 14 days of entering into this Agreement and WIN shall repay to the Distributor such monies as the Distributor may be legally entitled to recover within a reasonable period of time after the date of receipt of such notice.

    a) In order to recover monies paid for goods under paragraph 16(b) above, the Distributor must deliver the goods to WIN (upon receipt of a Return Merchandise Authrorisation) within 14 days of entering into this Agreement to WIN at the address set forth under 16(b) above. The Distributor shall bear the cost of such delivery. The monies paid in respect of those goods is payable to the Distributor on delivery of the goods or forthwith if the goods have not yet been delivered to the Distributor.
    b) WIN will not make a handling charge in respect of goods returned under paragraph 16(b) above or services cancelled under paragraph 16(c) above.

  18. If WIN terminates this Agreement, or if the Distributor terminates it after 14 days of entering into it, then the Distributor has the following rights:

    a) The Distributor shall be released from all future contractual obligations;
    b) The Distributor shall have the right to return to WIN any goods which the Distributor has purchased from WIN within a period of 90 days prior to such termination and which remain unsold and to recover from WIN: (1) where the Distributor has terminated the Agreement, the price (inclusive of value added tax) which the Distributor paid for them less (i) in the case of any goods the condition of which has deteriorated due to an act or default on the Distributor’s part, an amount equal to the diminution in their value resulting from such deterioration; and less (ii) a reasonable handling charge; (2) where WIN has terminated the Agreement the price (inclusive of value added tax) which the Distributor paid for them together with any costs incurred by the Distributor for returning the goods to WIN;
    c) The amount recoverable by the Distributor under this Clause 18 is payable by WIN upon delivery of the goods to it or, if the goods are already held by WIN, forthwith; and
    d) If the Distributor wishes to exercise the Distributor’s rights under this Clause 18 the Distributor must deliver any goods (not already held by WIN) which the Distributor wishes to return within 21 days of such termination to WIN at the address set forth under 16(b) above. The Distributor shall be reimbursed by WIN for the costs of such delivery.

  19. On termination of this Agreement for whatever reason the Distributor shall be entitled to retain any commission paid to him/her in accordance with this Agreement unless:
    a) the commission was paid in respect of goods returned to WIN; and
    b) WIN has refunded any monies due to the Distributor in accordance with the termination provisions of this Agreement set out above; and
    c) repayment of the commission is claimed by WIN within 120 days of its having been made in which case the Distributor shall repay such commission to WIN forthwith on demand or it may set−off the amount of such commission against any amounts due from it to the Distributor.

  20. If the Distributor elects not to renew this Agreement, or elects to cancel this Agreement, or if this Agreement is terminated by WIN, the Distributor’s rights to any commissions and his position in a line of sponsorship cease effective as of the date of non−renewal, cancellation, or termination. The Distributor understands that WIN reserves the right to assure continued service to the Distributor’s customers and that his personal sales organisation shall be forfeited and deemed transferred to his immediate upline sponsor, effective as of the date of non−renewal, cancellation, or termination. All provisions of this Agreement that provide rights or create responsibilities for the parties after termination of my distributorship and/or termination of this Agreement shall survive the termination of my distributorship and/or the termination of this Agreement for any reason. Such provisions that survive termination include, but not limited to, Terms 8, 10, 11, 20, 23, 27 and 31 of this Agreement and the United Kingdom Policies & Procedures covering Indemnity Agreement and Attorneys Fees, Covenant Not to Compete, Violations and Remedies, Confidentiality Agreement, Retail Customer Returns, No Reliance, Construction and Interpretation, Severability, Reservation of Rights, Venue; Governing Law; No Personal Liability, and Limitation of Liability.

    Nature of Agreement

  21. The Distributor has received a copy of and acknowledges that he has read and understands the WIN Policies & Procedures and the WIN Compensation Plan. The WIN Policies & Procedures and the WIN Compensation Plan are hereby incorporated by reference into this Agreement in their present form, and such documents may be amended by WIN from time to time. Any such amendments will be published in the appropriate Company literature and will become effective when announced by WIN regardless of the date on which the Distributor receives actual notice of the change provided that WIN shall give the Distributor at least 60 days notice of any change to the Distributor’s financial obligations under this Agreement. In the event of any conflict or inconsistency between this Agreement and any such other contractual documents, the terms of this Agreement shall prevail.

  22. The Distributor is a wholly independent distributor who establishes and services his customers as an independent contractor. This Agreement is not intended and shall not be construed to create a relationship of employer−employee, agency, partnership, or joint venture between the Distributor and any other distributor or sponsor(s), or WIN. The Distributor understands that WIN reserves no right to control or direct his efforts as a distributor.

  23. The liability of WIN, and of its partners and related entities and individuals, to the Distributor for any claim whatsoever related to the distributor relationship, including any cause of action founded in contract, tort, or strict liability, shall not exceed, and shall be limited to, the amount of unsold WIN product inventory owned by the Distributor at the relevant time. In no event shall WIN be liable to the Distributor for any incidental, special, exemplary, or consequential losses or damages.

  24. The Distributor is self−employed and is responsible for the expenses incurred by him in running his business including tax, national insurance contributions, and VAT.

  25. This Agreement (together with the WIN Policies & Procedures and the WIN Compensation Plan) constitutes the entire agreement between WIN and the Distributor, and no other promises, representations, guarantees, or agreements, nor alterations, modifications, or changes, of any kind, shall be valid unless in writing and signed by both parties, except as provided herein.

    Miscellaneous

  26. The Distributor cannot sell this WIN distributorship except under restrictions contained in the WIN Policies & Procedures.

  27. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of England and Wales and the parties hereto hereby submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the English Courts.

  28. Any notice given under this Agreement (including under the termination Clauses 15 to 18), which is given by first class post to the address of the parties at the head of this agreement or to such other address as shall have been notified from time to time in writing by one party to the other shall result in the period of notice commencing to run from the day when such notice is posted.

  29. In this Agreement references to the masculine gender shall include the feminine.

  30. The failure by WIN at any time to require performance by the Distributor of the provisions of this Agreement shall in no way affect its right to require the performance or remedy of any breach of any provisions of this Agreement and shall not be construed as a waiver of any continuing or succeeding breach of such provisions.

  31. Confidentiality − I understand that I shall hold all Confidential Information (including but not limited to genealogical downline or earnings reports of WIN, manufacturing or financial information, or any information obtained during the conduct of my WIN business) in strict confidence and shall not disclose, publish, sell or license the Confidential Information to any third party or use the Confidential Information in any manner not expressly permitted in writing by WIN. Upon termination or resignation of my distributorship for any reason, I agree promptly to return all Confidential Information to WIN.

  32. DOCUMENTS SIGNED BY FACSIMILE SIGNATURE — I authorize WIN to accept a facsimile, scanned or other electronic reproduction (“facsimile signature”) of my signature as my legally binding signature to the document of which it is a part.
